author: Min Zeng
title: U.S. Government Bonds Pull Back After Solid Housing Data
text:
U.S. government bonds pulled back Tuesday as a solid U.S. housing report drove investors to take some chips off the table from a recent rally.
In recent trading, the yield on the benchmark 10-year Treasury note was 2.198%, compared with 2.15% on Monday, according to Trade web. Yields rise as prices fall.
